# Rust Async Style

- Prefer asynchronous implementations whenever a code path may involve I/O, waiting, scheduling, downloading, browser automation, rule loading, or output/pipeline work.
- Do not introduce the `async_trait` crate.
- Use Rust native async directly on Rust `1.94.0`.
- When async abstraction is needed, prefer native async traits, concrete async methods, or explicit future types over macro-based async trait erasure.
- Keep synchronous code only for pure in-memory transforms, parsing helpers, and simple value/object utilities.
